AC   P96095;
Hydroxylamine reductase (EC 1.7.-.-) (Hybrid-cluster protein) (HCP).
"A geographically widespread plasmid from Thiobacillus ferrooxidans
has genes for ferredoxin-, FNR-, prismane- and NADH-oxidoreductase-
like proteins which are also located on the chromosome.";
-!- FUNCTION: Catalyzes the reduction of hydroxylamine to form NH(3)
    and H(2)O (By similarity).
-!- COFACTOR: Binds 1 2Fe-2S cluster (By similarity).
-!- COFACTOR: Binds 1 hybrid 4Fe-2O-2S cluster (By similarity).
-!- SUBCELLULAR LOCATION: Cytoplasm (By similarity).
-!- SIMILARITY: Belongs to the HCP family.
